 list of numbers in the `Fruits` column of the DataFrame.\n\t+ `labels = df['Colors']` specifies the labels for each wedge of the pie chart. These labels will be taken from the list of numbers in the `Colors` column of the DataFrame.\n\t+ `autopct='%1.1f%%'` is a parameter that formats the value displayed on each wedge of the pie chart. It displays the percentage value with one decimal place.\n\n### Displaying the Chart\n\n* The final line `plt.show()` displays the pie chart.\n\nNote: This code assumes that you have the necessary libraries installed, including `matplotlib` and `pandas`. If you haven't installed them yet, you can do so using pip: `pip install matplotlib pandas`."}]}